& [GateQuestion] is the low-resolution periphery
  + [question] is whether harmonic pressure can be treated as a controllable harmless remainder when trying to convert a pressure-tail budget into same-cylinder pressure L3_over_2 or pressure oscillation smallness
  + [reason_for_gate] is local artifacts marked harmonic pressure as implicit, high risk, and not extracted

& [SourceResolutionSet] is the clarified source neighborhood
  + [source_001_local_suitable_pressure_decomposition] is Wolf-style local suitable solution pressure decomposition
    = url: https://sebastian-hensel.com/master_thesis.pdf
    = reading: local pressure can be decomposed with a harmonic component, allowing local suitable solution frameworks without a globally defined pressure field
    = meaning_for_project: harmonic pressure must be named as its own component rather than hidden inside tail budget
    = limitation: decomposition vocabulary does not supply smallness of the harmonic part in the project regularity cylinder
  + [source_002_local_energy_epsilon_pressure_estimates] is Guevara-Phuc local energy and epsilon-regularity pressure-estimate framework
    = url: https://www.math.lsu.edu/~pcnguyen/papers_html/Guevara-Phuc-12-29-16.pdf
    = reading: local epsilon-regularity arguments track pressure quantities through local energy estimates and pressure-function spaces
    = meaning_for_project: the harmonic component must be compatible with the accepted pressure quantity, not merely bounded as a source-tail remainder
    = limitation: does not identify the project tail budget with the accepted pressure quantity
  + [source_003_harmonic_pressure_caution] is finite-scale one-component regularity via harmonic pressure
    = url: https://arxiv.org/abs/2606.08352
    = reading: a spatially harmonic pressure can have bounded scale-invariant L3_over_2 oscillation while its pointwise gradient becomes arbitrarily large under time concentration
    = meaning_for_project: pressure oscillation smallness or boundedness alone may not control the harmful aspect of harmonic pressure unless the theorem target is formulated modulo harmonic pressures or includes the correct remainder control
    = limitation: recent source; use as caution and periphery-shaping evidence, not as primary proof authority
  + [source_004_seregin_regular_regularization_survey] is Seregin survey on bounded scale-invariant quantities and epsilon regularity
    = url: https://ora.ox.ac.uk/objects/uuid%3Ae5f199d6-4981-44e2-9318-1db638e96e54/files/rx633f188s
    = reading: local regularity theory depends on suitable weak solutions and scale-invariant quantities for velocity and pressure on parabolic cylinders
    = meaning_for_project: harmonic pressure must be handled in the same scale-invariant framework, not as an external narrative remainder
    = limitation: survey context, not a project-tail conversion lemma

